  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tucked away in this fleshy abscess is a sculpture of a pickaxe embedded in a jumble of stone blocks. 

Near the sculpture's base is a bronze plaque.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>A metal pickaxe is embedded in a jumble of blocks. It might be your imagination, but the luster of the plaque at the base of the sculpture seems to have dimmed since you saw it last.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>The looted sculpture now stands as a lesson in unheeded hand-wringing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine the pickaxe.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Take the shins.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>Leave the sculpture alone.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>The shining metal handle towers overhead, completely out of reach. You couldn't touch it without climbing the sculpture itself, and even then, it looks far too heavy to move...

The pickaxe trembles, and you blink. You felt the motion in your mind. You may actually be able to affect this sculpture with your thoughts. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try to free the pickaxe.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>Leave it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh, *really*," Erritis says as you turn to go. "You know you can move a sculpture by staring at it, and you're not going to play with it?" He sighs. "No wonder you're so glum all the time."

Suddenly, he perks up. "How about *I* give it a try?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>There are more important things to do than wrangling mining tools.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hold on. Let me think about it some more."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Go ahead."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No, don't touch it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>Clenching his fists, Erritis *glares* at the sculpture. Seconds pass. He bares his teeth, growling. 

With a hoarse scraping sound, the pickaxe retracts from the blocks, and a waterfall of shins cascades from some hidden recess into a pile between the blocks. 

Erritis beams, panting. "Sculptures are no match for the mental prowess of Erritis!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>You focus on the handle of the pickaxe and think,  "Move." It twitches, but nothing else happens.

Shutting out every sound around you, every tremor in the floor, and the soft thumping of your heart, you pit your full attention against the shape of the tool above you.  

With a hoarse scraping sound, the pickaxe retracts from the stone blocks, and a waterfall of shins cascades from some inner recess in the sculpture into a pile between the blocks. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Straining your mind, you imagine the pickaxe moving beneath the firm hand of your thoughts. It shudders once, then goes still again. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Erritis tsks slightly - just loud enough to make sure you hear it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You won a battle of wits with a sculpture!" Erritis gasps. "Congratulations!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>::grumbles::</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine the plaque.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>Read the plaque again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>Etched on the plaque is a short message.

*Better to swing the pick than strike the vein:
shins are shackles and treasures chains.*</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Written like a man who's never felt the rasp of poverty," Tybir mutters.

{GAVIN: Voice?}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you reach for the shins inside the sculpture, a strange feeling of revulsion sweeps over you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>Even in a treasure hoard, a pile of shins sitting on a pedestal smacks of a trap. Better to leave it be.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>Take them anyway.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>Pull your hand back.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>You quickly scoop up the shins. With each handful, the queasiness seems to sink deeper into you, fogging your thoughts. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>The unnerving feeling passes the moment you draw your hand away.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try to free the pickaxe.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try to free the pickaxe again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Think? What adventure ever arose from *that*?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Erritis, see if you can free that pickaxe."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ha ha! Prepare to meet your match, inanimate tool!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>You concentrate hard on the pickaxe, willing it to move, bit it still doesn't budge.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We're leaving?" Erritis says, horrified. "But what about all the treasure?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tybir chuckles, long and low. 

"Spoken like someone who dislikes their money *and* shackles. I don't think the artist and I would have gotten along."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are we *really* leaving that treasure behind?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes. Let's go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>::sighs::</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"All right, Erritis. You can 'play' with the statue."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
